api

Class OAuth1NoCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • api.OAuth1Generic
      • api.OAuth1NoCallback

  • public class OAuth1NoCallback
extends OAuth1Generic
    An OAuth1.0 consumer class, using the HMAC signing api.strategy.

    This is a consumer which does not support a callback.

    Usage:
    1. Call begin() to obtain a temporary token and a redirect URL if OAuth1Generic.authoriseUrl was provided (not null).
    2. On the front-end, redirect the user to the redirect URL obtained in (1), or compute the redirect URL from the temporary token obtained in (1).
    3. Once the user has granted access on the redirect URL, call authorised(String) with the temporary token obtained in (1).
    4. If (3) succeeded, you now have an access token and an OAuthParameters object that can be used to make requests on the user's behalf. Using the OAuthParameters make a request to a given URL with a given HTTP request method and body via OAuth1Generic.makeOAuthBackedRequest(String, OAuthParameters, RequestMethod, HttpContent).
    Author:
    Omar Tanner
